\f1\fs32 Closing the main contacts completes the circuit between the power supply and the motor, allowing current to flow directly to the motor's terminals and start the motor.\
Since the auxiliary contact is  wired in parallel with the start button, after it closes the start button may be released and the motor will continue to operate.  For this reason, the auxiliary contact is sometimes called the 
\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::4>
\f2\b\fs32 latch
