\f0\fs24 \AppleTypeServices \cf5 <!$Scr_Ps::1><$Scr_Ps::3>
\f3\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 The 
\f0\fs24 \AppleTypeServices \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\b\fs28 stop button
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf5 <!$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  is pressed.  This breaks the control circuit and de-energizes the main coil.  This causes the main and auxiliary contacts to open and stop the motor.\
One of the three 
\f0\fs24 \AppleTypeServices \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\b\fs28 overload sensors
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf5 <!$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  detects the motor drawing high current.  This opens the corresponding 
\f0\fs24 \AppleTypeServices \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\b\fs28 overload contact
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf5 <!$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  in the control circuit and stops the motor.\
A 
\f0\fs24 \AppleTypeServices \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\b\fs28 short circuit
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf5 <!$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  is detected by the 
\f0\fs24 \AppleTypeServices \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\b\fs28 circuit breaker
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf5 <!$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 , tripping it.  This secures power to both the power and control circuits and stops the motor.  Fuses will de-energize the control circuit if a short occurs there.\
A 
\f0\fs24 \AppleTypeServices \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\b\fs28 low voltage condition
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf5 <!$Scr_Cs::4>
\f3\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  occurs when the supply voltage drops below about 90% of its nominal value.  If this happens, the current through the operating coil decreases, causing its electromagnet to weaken enough to release the main contacts, which stops the motor.  If the voltage returns to normal, the motor will remain stopped until the start button is pressed again.\
